cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.SD, cs.CL

The paper focuses on self-supervised learning for feature representations using data transformations, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of multi-modal data transformations also suggests a potential fit for the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Additionally, the paper evaluates its method on downstream classification tasks, which could fall under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the use of a contrastive loss function for training could also suggest a fit for the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
